trpzClientSessionMib.name: trpzClientSessionMib

revisions.description: v3.1.2: Added three new columnar objects: trpzClSessClientSessDeviceType, trpzClSessClientSessDeviceGroup, trpzClSessClientSessDeviceProfileName. (for 8.0 release)
v3.1.0: Added a new table: trpzClSessClientAddressTable to hold the clients' Internet addresses. (for 8.0 release)
v3.0.0: Obsoleted a previously deprecated object: 'trpzClSessClientSessAuthMethod' and the associated Textual Convention: 'TrpzAuthMethod'. This will be published in 7.5 release.
v2.4.1: Using the new TC TrpzPhysPortNumberOrZero instead of ''Unsigned32 (0..1024)''. This will be published in 7.1 release.
v2.4.0: Updated conformance section to reflect the history of changes to this MIB: added more compliance statements and groups. This will be published in 7.0 release.
v2.3.4: Added two new columnar objects: - trpzClSessClientSessPhysPortNum, - trpzClSessRoamHistPhysPortNum, to indicate the port used by wired-auth clients. (for 6.2 release)

v2.3.1: Added four new columnar objects: - trpzClSessClientSessAccessMode, obsoleting trpzClSessClientSessAccessType; - trpzClSessClientSessApNum, obsoleting trpzClSessClientSessPortOrNum; - trpzClSessRoamHistAccessMode, obsoleting trpzClSessRoamHistAccessType; - trpzClSessRoamHistApNum, obsoleting trpzClSessRoamHistApNumOrPort. Reason: in 6.0, direct- and network-attached APs were unified. (for 6.2 release)
v2.2.1: added one value (21) to TrpzSessState

v2.1.1: Added three new columnar objects: - trpzClSessClientSessDot1xAuthMethod, to be used instead of trpzClSessClientSessAuthMethod; - trpzClSessClientSessSessionState, to be used instead of trpzClSessClientSessState; - trpzClSessClientSessLoginType, to provide context for interpreting the values of the above objects (Dot1xAuthMethod, SessionState). Changed behaviour for trpzClSessClientSessAuthServer: provides system IP when auth is done via local DB (it used to be 0.0.0.0 in such cases).
v2.0.2: Fixed imports and compliance group
v2.0.1: Adding scalar for total number of sessions.

trpzClSessClientSessionEntry.name: trpzClSessClientSessionEntry
trpzClSessClientSessionEntry.description: Information about a particular client session.

trpzClSessClientSessSessionId.name: trpzClSessClientSessSessionId
trpzClSessClientSessSessionId.description: Session ID is a string long enough to be sure we can make it unique over a long time.

trpzClSessClientSessIpAddress.name: trpzClSessClientSessIpAddress
trpzClSessClientSessIpAddress.description: Client IP address. If the client has no IP address, the value will be 0.0.0.0.

trpzClSessClientSessVlan.name: trpzClSessClientSessVlan
trpzClSessClientSessVlan.description: The name of the client VLAN.

trpzClSessClientSessApSerialNum.name: trpzClSessClientSessApSerialNum
trpzClSessClientSessApSerialNum.description: Serial Number of the AP this client is connected to. It is a zero length string when wired access is used.

trpzClSessClientSessRadioNum.name: trpzClSessClientSessRadioNum
trpzClSessClientSessRadioNum.description: Number of the Radio that provides service to this client. It is 'not-applicable' when wired access is used.

trpzClSessClientSessAccessType.name: trpzClSessClientSessAccessType
trpzClSessClientSessAccessType.description: Access type this client uses (via AP, DAP or wired). Obsoleted by trpzClSessClientSessAccessMode.

trpzClSessClientSessAuthMethod.name: trpzClSessClientSessAuthMethod
trpzClSessClientSessAuthMethod.description: Authentication Method. Obsolete, use trpzClSessClientSessDot1xAuthMethod instead.

trpzClSessClientSessAuthServer.name: trpzClSessClientSessAuthServer
trpzClSessClientSessAuthServer.description: Authentication Server's IP Address. If the client is authenticated via the local DB, or not authenticated, its value will be the system IP.

trpzClSessClientSessState.name: trpzClSessClientSessState
trpzClSessClientSessState.description: Session state. Deprecated, use trpzClSessClientSessSessionState instead.

trpzClSessClientSessLoginType.name: trpzClSessClientSessLoginType
trpzClSessClientSessLoginType.description: Login type (mac, web, dot1x or last-resort).

trpzClSessClientSessAccessMode.name: trpzClSessClientSessAccessMode
trpzClSessClientSessAccessMode.description: Access mode (type) this client uses (via AP or wired). Obsoletes trpzClSessClientSessAccessType since in 6.0 directly attached APs and DAPs were unified.

trpzClSessClientSessApNum.name: trpzClSessClientSessApNum
trpzClSessClientSessApNum.description: The AP providing wireless service to this client is identified by its administratively assigned AP Number, unique on same AC (switch), regardless of how APs are attached to the AC. Meaningful when trpzClSessClientSessAccessMode = 'ap'. Obsoletes trpzClSessClientSessPortOrNum since in 6.0 directly attached APs and DAPs were unified.

trpzClSessClientSessPhysPortNum.name: trpzClSessClientSessPhysPortNum
trpzClSessClientSessPhysPortNum.description: The physical port used by this wired-auth client is identified by its port number on the AC (switch). Zero means the port is unknown or not applicable (for example, when trpzClSessClientSessAccessMode = 'ap'). Meaningful when trpzClSessClientSessAccessMode = 'wired'.

trpzClSessClientSessDeviceType.name: trpzClSessClientSessDeviceType
trpzClSessClientSessDeviceType.description: The type of the client device. Is a zero length string if unknown or the device detection feature is disabled.

trpzClSessClientSessDeviceGroup.name: trpzClSessClientSessDeviceGroup
trpzClSessClientSessDeviceGroup.description: The group that the detected client device type belongs to. Is a zero length string if the device type is unknown or the device detection feature is disabled.

trpzClSessClientSessDeviceProfileName.name: trpzClSessClientSessDeviceProfileName
trpzClSessClientSessDeviceProfileName.description: The name of the device profile associated with the detected client device. A device profile is a collection of policies that apply to one or more types of client devices. Is a zero length string in 'detect-only' mode, if not set or if the device detection feature is disabled. In 'detect-only' mode policy enforcement is disabled.

trpzClSessRoamingHistoryTable.name: trpzClSessRoamingHistoryTable
trpzClSessRoamingHistoryTable.description: Roaming History Table. Expansion of Client Session Table.

trpzClSessRoamHistApSerialNum.name: trpzClSessRoamHistApSerialNum
trpzClSessRoamHistApSerialNum.description: Serial Number of the AP this client was connected to.

trpzClSessRoamHistRadioNum.name: trpzClSessRoamHistRadioNum
trpzClSessRoamHistRadioNum.description: Number of the Radio that provided service to this client.

trpzClSessRoamHistAccessType.name: trpzClSessRoamHistAccessType
trpzClSessRoamHistAccessType.description: Access type used by this client (via AP, DAP or wired). Obsoleted by trpzClSessRoamHistAccessMode.

trpzClSessRoamHistApNumOrPort.name: trpzClSessRoamHistApNumOrPort
trpzClSessRoamHistApNumOrPort.description: AP port number, DAP number, or Port number for wired access. Obsoleted by trpzClSessRoamHistApNum.

trpzClSessRoamHistIpAddress.name: trpzClSessRoamHistIpAddress
trpzClSessRoamHistIpAddress.description: IP address of the AC (wireless switch) the client or AP was connected to.

trpzClSessRoamHistTimeStamp.name: trpzClSessRoamHistTimeStamp
trpzClSessRoamHistTimeStamp.description: The difference between the time the session was created on the roamed-to switch and the time the last switch, the one where the user is at currently, started. The timestamp unit is in hundredths of seconds.

trpzClSessRoamHistAccessMode.name: trpzClSessRoamHistAccessMode
trpzClSessRoamHistAccessMode.description: Access mode (type) used by this client (via AP or wired). Obsoletes trpzClSessRoamHistAccessType since in 6.0 directly attached APs and DAPs were unified.

trpzClSessRoamHistApNum.name: trpzClSessRoamHistApNum
trpzClSessRoamHistApNum.description: The administratively assigned AP Number, unique on same AC (switch), regardless of how APs are attached to the AC. Obsoletes trpzClSessRoamHistApNumOrPort since in 6.0 directly attached APs and DAPs were unified.

trpzClSessRoamHistPhysPortNum.name: trpzClSessRoamHistPhysPortNum
trpzClSessRoamHistPhysPortNum.description: The physical port used by this wired-auth client is identified by its port number on the AC (switch). Zero means the port is unknown or not applicable (for example, when trpzClSessRoamHistAccessMode = 'ap'). Meaningful when trpzClSessRoamHistAccessMode = 'wired'.

trpzClSessClientSessStatsEncErrPkt.name: trpzClSessClientSessStatsEncErrPkt
trpzClSessClientSessStatsEncErrPkt.description: Number of packets with encryption errors.

trpzClSessClientSessStatsEncErrOctet.name: trpzClSessClientSessStatsEncErrOctet
trpzClSessClientSessStatsEncErrOctet.description: Number of octets with encryption errors.

trpzClSessClientSessStatsLastRssi.name: trpzClSessClientSessStatsLastRssi
trpzClSessClientSessStatsLastRssi.description: RSSI (Received Signal Strength Indicator) for last packet, in decibels referred to 1 milliwatt (dBm). A higher value indicates a stronger signal.

trpzClSessClientSessStatsLastSNR.name: trpzClSessClientSessStatsLastSNR
trpzClSessClientSessStatsLastSNR.description: Last packet data Signal to Noise Ratio.

trpzClSessClientAddressTable.name: trpzClSessClientAddressTable
trpzClSessClientAddressTable.description: Client Address Table. This table contains the clients' Internet addresses. Each client may have one IPv4 address, one IPv6 link-local address and multiple IPv6 global addresses. Expansion of the Client Session Table.

trpzClSessClientAddressEntry.name: trpzClSessClientAddressEntry
trpzClSessClientAddressEntry.description: An entry in the Client Address table. A client's MAC address together with an unsigned integer uniquely identify one of that client's Internet addresses.

trpzClSessClientAddressIndex.name: trpzClSessClientAddressIndex
trpzClSessClientAddressIndex.description: Last part of the composite index of the Client Address table. The client is identified by the first part of the composite index: 'trpzClSessClientSessMacAddress'. Index 1 corresponds to the IPv4 address of the client. Index 2 corresponds to the IPv6 link-local address of the client. Indexes 3-9 are reserved for future use. Indexes starting at 10 correspond to IPv6 global addresses of the client; the number of IPv6 addresses per client may vary.

trpzClSessClientAddressValue.name: trpzClSessClientAddressValue
trpzClSessClientAddressValue.description: Client Internet address. The type of this address is specified in 'trpzClSessClientAddressType'.

trpzClientSessionCompliance.name: trpzClientSessionCompliance
trpzClientSessionCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices that implement the Client Session MIB. This compliance statement was for releases 4.1 and 4.2 of AC (wireless switch) software. This compliance statement is replaced by trpzClientSessionComplianceRev2.

trpzClientSessionComplianceRev2.name: trpzClientSessionComplianceRev2
trpzClientSessionComplianceRev2.description: The compliance statement for devices that implement the Client Session MIB. This compliance statement was for releases 5.0 and 6.0 of AC (wireless switch) software. This compliance statement is replaced by trpzClientSessionComplianceRev3.

trpzClientSessionComplianceRev3.name: trpzClientSessionComplianceRev3
trpzClientSessionComplianceRev3.description: The compliance statement for devices that implement the Client Session MIB. This compliance statement is for releases 6.2 to 7.7 of AC (wireless switch) software. This compliance statement is replaced by trpzClientSessionComplianceRev4.

trpzClientSessionComplianceRev4.name: trpzClientSessionComplianceRev4
trpzClientSessionComplianceRev4.description: The compliance statement for devices that implement the Client Session MIB. This compliance statement is for releases 8.0 and greater of AC (wireless switch) software.

trpzClientSessionCommonGroup.name: trpzClientSessionCommonGroup
trpzClientSessionCommonGroup.description: Mandatory group of objects implemented to provide Client Session info in releases 4.1 and 4.2 of AC (wireless switch) software. Replaced by trpzClientSessClientSessionTableGroup, trpzClientSessRoamingHistoryTableGroup, trpzClientSessClientSessionStatisticsTableGroup.

trpzClientSessScalarsGroup.name: trpzClientSessScalarsGroup
trpzClientSessScalarsGroup.description: Group of scalar objects implemented to provide general Client info in releases 5.0 and greater.

trpzClientSessClientSessionTableGroup.name: trpzClientSessClientSessionTableGroup
trpzClientSessClientSessionTableGroup.description: Group of columnar objects implemented to provide Client Session info in releases 5.0 and 6.0. Replaced by trpzClientSessClientSessionTableGroupRev2.

trpzClientSessRoamingHistoryTableGroup.name: trpzClientSessRoamingHistoryTableGroup
trpzClientSessRoamingHistoryTableGroup.description: Group of columnar objects implemented to provide roaming history per Client Session in releases 5.0 and 6.0. Replaced by trpzClientSessRoamingHistoryTableGroupRev2.

trpzClientSessClientSessionStatisticsTab.name: trpzClientSessClientSessionStatisticsTableGroup
trpzClientSessClientSessionStatisticsTab.description: Group of columnar objects implemented to provide statistics per Client Session in releases 5.0 and greater.

trpzClientSessClientSessionTableGroupRev.name: trpzClientSessClientSessionTableGroupRev2
trpzClientSessClientSessionTableGroupRev.description: Group of columnar objects implemented to provide Client Session info in releases 6.2 to 7.7.

trpzClientSessRoamingHistoryTableGroupRe.name: trpzClientSessRoamingHistoryTableGroupRev2
trpzClientSessRoamingHistoryTableGroupRe.description: Group of columnar objects implemented to provide roaming history per Client Session in releases 6.2 and greater.

trpzClSessClientAddressTableGroup.name: trpzClSessClientAddressTableGroup
trpzClSessClientAddressTableGroup.description: Group of columnar objects implemented to provide a complete listing of the clients' Internet addresses in releases 8.0 and greater.

trpzClientSessClientSessionTableGroupRev.name: trpzClientSessClientSessionTableGroupRev3
trpzClientSessClientSessionTableGroupRev.description: Group of columnar objects implemented to provide Client Session info in releases 8.0 and greater.
